The paper deals with relay scheduling in communication networks, which is a topic closely related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of submodular functions and linear programming, which are common tools in network optimization (cs.NI). The paper's focus on the structural properties of optimal solutions suggests that it may also be relevant to the field of structural informatics (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper's use of mathematical proofs and algorithms suggests that it may be relevant to the fields of data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
